# This file is NOT read by anything — Turborepo doesn't inject a root
# .env into child packages, and WXT (the extension's build tool) only
# reads .env relative to its own package directory. It's left here only
# because it's the first place people look; the real files are:
#
#   apps/extension/.env   <- copy from apps/extension/.env.example
#   apps/backend/.env     <- copy from apps/backend/.env.example
#
# See those two files for what actually goes in each.

